Delaware State Police, Delaware

End of Watch Friday, January 22, 1971

Add to My Heroes

William C. Keller

Trooper William Keller was killed in an automobile accident while en route to an undercover assignment in Dover.

His undercover vehicle was struck by a garbage truck on US 13 near Tybouts Corner. He succumbed to his injuries en route to a local hospital.

Trooper Keller had served with the Delaware State Police for two years. He is survived by his wife and daughter.
